<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="864" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d864">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.48/1050: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Viborg</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Imbrie</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Viborg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-15"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                    1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received December 16, 5:51
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>165. <persName corresp="#p_YGNN1">Yudenitch</persName> requests that
                            Viborg stores with exception of 4,000 tons, about one week’s supply for
                            Petrograd, be sent Reval at once as his army and refugees in great
                            distress. Last of American Relief at Reval confirms need of food and
                            advises sending Viborg stores, also states that no American Relief
                            stores expected at Reval.</p>
                        <p>Request immediate instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Imbrie</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>